Class Description
DynamicPlugin
"DynamicPlugin" is a abstract-class for all dynamic plugins that print don't return static files.
ErrorPlugin
The Error plugin is responsible to return a 404 page if no other plugin can handle the request.
H2DBService
Can be used to access the H2 Database that contains the temperature data of the sensor
IPlugin  
IPluginManager  
IRequest  
IResponse  
IUrl  
NaviPlugin
Is capable of searching for city names based on an entered street name
PluginManager
Is capable of loading plugin dynamically at runtime from class files.
Request
httpRequest takes an InputStream containing a HTTP Request validates it by RegExp and gathers all segments
Response
Response serves as an Object for creating an OutputStream to send it to the client socket
ResponseFactory
Can be used for different builds of a HttpResponse, like if you don't set a statusCode it 200 by default
Sensor
A single Runnable that simulates a temperature sensor.
StaticPlugin
"StaticPlugin" is a full-functional, low priority plugin for loading static files.
Temperature
A class that serves as interchangeable object between the sensor and the H2 Database
TemperaturePlugin
Is capable of running a simulated sensor that reads the current temperature and accessing a H2 Database that contains 10.000 temperature data sets
TestPlugin  
ToLowerPlugin
Is capable of transforming a String to a lowercase String
Url
Serves as data container and parser of an URL
